<page xmlns="http://projectmallard.org/1.0/"
      type="topic"
      id="QuickStartGuide">
      <title> Quick Start </title>
      <p>
        This guide will quickly, in 8 steps, show how to get started once you installed GMPC.
        This guide assumes that you allready setup MPD and it is working.
      </p>
      <steps>
        <item>
            <title>Step 1</title>
            <p>
                Start GMPC. Normally GMPC can be found in the menu under: 
                <code>Applications->Multimedia->Gnome Music Player Client</code>
                This should be identical under GNOME, KDE, Unitiy and XFCE.
                If you start it from a terminal, or using a run dialog (alt-F2) type
                <code>gmpc</code>
            </p>
            <figure>
                <media type="image" src="Images/gmpc-dev-install-guidestep_9.png"/>
            </figure>
        </item>
        <item>
            <title>Step 2</title>
            <p>
                The first time you run gmpc, you see a first-run wizard.
                Follow the wizard step by step.
             </p>
             <note>
                <p>
                    If you do not get the wizard. You can get the same connection pane, by 
                    going to the preferences.  <code>Music->Preferences</code>.
                </p>
             </note>
            <figure>
            <media type="image" src="Images/gmpc-dev-install-guidestep_10.png"/>
            </figure>
        </item>
        <item>
            <title>Step 3</title>
            <p>
                Enter the ip of the machine running mpd.
                If GMPC and MPD are running on the same machine, you can enter 
                <code>localhost</code> in the Host field.
                If MPD is running on a different machine, enter the external IP address of that machine.
                In the screenshot this is <code>192.150.0.102</code>
            </p>
            <note>
                <p>
                    If you password protected your MPD, enable <code>Use Authentication</code>
                    and enter the password below.
                </p>
            </note>
            <figure>
            <media type="image" src="Images/gmpc-dev-install-guidestep_11.png"/>
            </figure>
            <p>
                Press Connect, if that succeeds, we can continue to the final page of the wizard.
            </p>
            <p>
                If GMPC fails to connect to MPD, check if MPD is running.
                If MPD is running on a different machine, check if MPD accepts connections from the network.
                This is configured with the <code>bind_to_address</code> option in <code>mpd.conf</code>.
            </p>
        </item>
        <item>
            <title>Step 4</title>
            <p>
                If GMPC is successfully connected we can close the wizard.
            </p>
            <figure>
            <media type="image" src="Images/gmpc-dev-install-guidestep_12.png"/>
            </figure>

        </item>
        <item>
            <title>Step 5</title>
            <note>
                <p>
                    If you already add music to the play queue from another client you will
                    see this play queue in GMPC. Clients are kept into sync with each other.
                </p>
            </note>
            <p>
                (update screenshots)
            </p>
            <p>
                When running GMPC for the first time we see the now playing screen.
                This does not display anything because no music is currently playing.
            </p>
            <figure>
            <media type="image" src="Images/gmpc-dev-install-guidestep_13.png"/>
            </figure>
            <p>
                Lets add some music, the easiest way is using the file browser (called Database).
                You can find the database in the left pane.
            </p>
        </item>
        <item>
            <title>Step 6</title>
            <figure>
                <media type="image" src="Images/gmpc-dev-install-guidestep_14.png"/>
            </figure>
            <note>
                <p>
                    If you see no folders or music in the Database, it means MPD has not indexed your music.
                    To let MPD index your music go the the <code>Server</code> menu and press <code>Update MPD Database</code>.
                    In the lower right corner a updating icon will appear.  If after updating the database view is still empty
                    you might want to check the MPD documentation on how to solve this.
                </p>
           </note>
        </item>
        <item>
            <title>Step 7</title>
            <p>
                To add a songs you right-click on the folder and press add.
            </p>
            <figure>
                <media type="image" src="Images/gmpc-dev-install-guidestep_15.png"/>
            </figure>
        </item>
        <item>
            <title>Step 8</title>
            <p>
                Now the play queue is filled, lets select a song an play it. (double click on the song).
            </p>
            <figure>
                <media type="image" src="Images/gmpc-dev-install-guidestep_16.png"/>
            </figure>
        </item>
    </steps>
</page>
